abstract: Ambitious moves to shift power to workers are being embraced by several Democratic presidential contenders.
snippet: Ambitious moves to shift power to workers are being embraced by several Democratic presidential contenders.
lead_paragraph: When Bernie Sanders ran for president in 2016, his campaign was strikingly pro-labor. He proposed a $15-an-hour minimum wage, which was much further than most mainstream Democrats, including Hillary Clinton, were willing to go. He denounced a trans-Pacific trade deal that was anathema to many unions. He endorsed an organizing method, known as card check, that would allow workers to unionize without holding a secret-ballot election.

abstract: The presidential debates will be held in Indiana, Michigan and Tennessee, and a vice-presidential debate will be held in Utah.
snippet: The presidential debates will be held in Indiana, Michigan and Tennessee, and a vice-presidential debate will be held in Utah.
lead_paragraph: The nonpartisan commission that governs presidential debates announced on Friday the dates and sites for the three presidential debates and one vice-presidential debate during the 2020 general election.

abstract: Activists at the Equality Town Hall repeatedly called on the 2020 Democrats to focus more on violence against transgender women of color.
snippet: Activists at the Equality Town Hall repeatedly called on the 2020 Democrats to focus more on violence against transgender women of color.
lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES â€” During a nationally televised forum on Thursday focusing on gay, lesbian, bisexual and transgender issues, several Democratic presidential candidates were interrupted by transgender activists who repeatedly called for more focus on the murders of black transgender women and said that the forum had not done enough to include their voices.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee announced that the debate would be held in the Atlanta area on Nov. 20, hosted by MSNBC and The Washington Post.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee announced that the debate would be held in the Atlanta area on Nov. 20, hosted by MSNBC and The Washington Post.
lead_paragraph: The fifth Democratic presidential debate of the 2020 campaign will be held in the Atlanta area on Wednesday, Nov. 20, the Democratic National Committee announced on Tuesday. MSNBC and The Washington Post will host it.
